// NOTE: SyncThing only auto-loads .stignore at the share root, not here.
// The actual exclusion patterns live in:
//   /home/jdelay/SyncThing/.stignore                    (Storage share root)
//   /home/jdelay/SyncThing/Obsidian/TheDeLay/.stignore  (Obsidian share root)
//
// This file is project-level documentation explaining what's excluded and
// why, so future-you reading the project knows the policy without spelunking
// share roots. If you change the exclusions, mirror them in BOTH share roots.
//
// What's excluded:
//   data/        the SQLite DB; multi-host writes would conflict + lose data
//   .env         Spotify credentials; one host should hold them
//   logs/        per-run logs; meaningless on other hosts
//   .venv/       host-specific Python binaries; large, useless to sync
//   __pycache__/ + .pytest_cache/  caches; rebuilt on demand
//
// What still syncs:
//   scripts/, sql/, tests/, README.md, INSTALL.md, etc. — convenient for
//   editing across machines
//   .git/ — intentionally NOT excluded; this is the canonical workspace
